I have the following in my zshrc for sudo. It adds sudo at the beginning of the current line or writes sudo !! if the current line is empty. I've aliased it to alt+s<p><pre><code>    run-with-sudo() {
      if [[ -z $LBUFFER ]]; then
        LBUFFER="sudo !!";
      else
        LBUFFER="sudo $LBUFFER";
      fi
    };
    zle -N run-with-sudo;
    bindkey '\es' run-with-sudo</code></pre>
